getGrounding

public UPnPGrounding getGrounding()
Description copied from interface: AtomicGrounding
Get the enclosing grounding this atomic process grounding belongs to. If it is referenced by more than one grounding pick one arbitrarily.

In OWL-S every atomic process grounding is enclosed by an instance of the concept OWLS.Grounding#Grounding.

Specified by:

invoke

public java.util.concurrent.Future<ValueMap<Output,OWLValue>> invoke(ValueMap<Input,OWLValue> values)
Description copied from interface: AtomicGrounding
Invoke this grounding with the given input values.

This method is supposed to return immediately for groundings providing asynchronous invocation. For groundings providing synchronous invocation this method may or may not return immediately (a subsequent get on the Future returned is required anyway).

Specified by:
invoke in interface AtomicGrounding<java.lang.String>
Parameters:
values - Values bound to the input parameters of the backing process.
Returns:
Future representing pending completion of the invocation. The Future's get method will return the values bound to output parameters of the backing atomic process (i.e. the outputs produced by the process) upon successful completion. Otherwise, an ExecutionException is thrown which possibly wraps a causing exception.

invoke

public java.util.concurrent.Future<ValueMap<Output,OWLValue>> invoke(ValueMap<Input,OWLValue> inputs,
                                                                     OWLKnowledgeBase env)
Description copied from interface: AtomicGrounding
Invoke this grounding with the given input values and use the given KB to store the output values.

This method is supposed to return immediately for groundings providing asynchronous invocation. For groundings providing synchronous invocation this method may or may not return immediately (a subsequent get on the Future returned is required anyway).

Specified by:
invoke in interface AtomicGrounding<java.lang.String>
Parameters:
inputs - Values bound to the input parameters of the backing process.
env - The execution environment to which output values will be added.
Returns:
Future representing pending completion of the invocation. The Future's get method will return the values bound to output parameters of the backing atomic process (i.e. the outputs produced by the process) upon successful completion. Otherwise, an ExecutionException is thrown which possibly wraps a causing exception.
